Hi guys,

My git repository is notifying DeployHQ twice for every time I push (https://bitbucket.org/aronsteg/smsd/). It&#x27;s causing me problem with processes getting restarted twice. Can you help fix it please?

{code}
A.
{code}

All you need to do is add one line of css to the {{.refract-container .source}}:

{code:css}
.refract-container .source {
  padding-left: 73px;
  tab-size: 2; // Add this line
}
{code}

It doesn&#x27;t screw up anything and makes tab-indented code look much better.

When a commit is made to any branch. Newsfeed and Recent Activity notifications do not include name of the branch. However, HipChat notification includes such information. Newsfeed should also include this extra information.

*In Newsfeed or Recent Activity Listing*

{code}
#!markdown

XYZ committed to xyz/my_repo
4 hours ago
4ac0c56 - more minor edits for some markdown syntax
{code}

*But in Hipchat*

{code}
#!markdown

XYZ committed to 1 branch at /xyz/my_repo/
On branch "readme_update"
- more minor edits for some markdown syntax (4ac0c56bd5f7)
{code}
